{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Description*

During the new reactivation flow UAT, we found a bug that happens when the user changes their zip code to a different one that does not offer the same delivery dates as the previous one.

We currently are not validating the available delivery dates when there is an address change, and we actually allow the user to proceed with the reactivation with a wrong delivery date, which will cause issues.

So when the user is editing their delivery address on the reactivation page, we should validate that their delivery option is a valid delivery option according to their zip code, and if it‚Äôs not, then we should update the delivery option.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#ffebe6}
*Out of Scope* 

* If applicable, when the task/feature is split into multiple tickets
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria* *_(focus on the what, not the how)_*

WHEN I am a deactivated user

AND I am on the /plan-reactivation page

AND I change my zip code to a different one that does not offer the same delivery slot I had previously selected

THEN my delivery slot should be changed to the first available delivery slot according to my zip code
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*Developer Information* 

* Does it require [release log|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Y9ZsoBL6vLG_HwEfAKSleYNHIslCTlEeAaJpU1c0evg/edit?gid=1092559263#gid=1092559263] record? (add ticket label: release-log)
* Do you recommend mobbing/pairing on this ticket?
* If applicable, caveats or other known dependencies
* Code context - examples of implementation
* ‚ö†Ô∏è If possible, avoid using redux and try to refactor the files you‚Äôre touching that depend on redux to use data access hooks. E.g to get subscription data you can use [this hook|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/a5dcf829594c11a7355ad1df3844ca898be17aba/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/libraries/data-access/subscription/useCurrentSubscription.ts]  ‚ö†Ô∏è
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Description*

When user is editing their delivery window (i.e. delivery day) we currently filter the delivery options based on cadence, E.g. if it‚Äôs a plan that should have a 4 week cadence, we filter the options to only return anything with {{*-4WEEKLY}}. As on of the first steps in deprecating the cadence delivery options, we want to filter out all cadence delivery options that have cadence in them (anything with {{WEEKLY}} at the end). This should be behind a feature flag for now.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#ffebe6}
*Out of Scope* 

* If applicable, when the task/feature is split into multiple tickets
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria* *_(focus on the what, not the how)_*

* If feature flag is on: 
** User us always assigned to a non-cadence delivery option
** User‚Äôs cadence is set correctly
** Users that are already on a cadence delivery option should
*** Be able to see their delivery day on /settings/plan
*** User can still change delivery days
* If feature flag is off (BAU): 
** User us always assigned to the appropriate cadence delivery option
** User‚Äôs cadence is set correctly
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*Developer Information* 

* The relevant code that needs to be changed should be mostly TPT specific but good to double check
* This is a good place to start from [https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/master/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/pages/settings/src/components/PlanSettings/DeliveryWindow/MultiPet/DeliveryWindowDropdown.tsx|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/master/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/pages/settings/src/components/PlanSettings/DeliveryWindow/MultiPet/DeliveryWindowDropdown.tsx] 
* Feature gate: [https://console.statsig.com/VNhnT1dlnFGbNlAloFMfp/gates/tpt_deprecate_cadence_delivery_options|https://console.statsig.com/VNhnT1dlnFGbNlAloFMfp/gates/tpt_deprecate_cadence_delivery_options|smart-link] 
{panel}

